{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":29920,"record_hash":"sha256:2c9811552ac7ec77466af10d61e926a90529d3206d7644c8bd1aa5acf2edf152","timestamp":"2026-05-11T16:18:48.678Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"assistant","text":"Yes, GitMeta has a set structure, and we are already using it for dedupe-adjacent things:\n\n- `gitbutler:agent-sessions` is a set of session keys.\n- `...:sources` is a set of source keys.\n- `...:record-hashes` is a set of captured transcript record hashes.\n\nSo the current shape is basically:\n\n```text\n:transcript      = ordered list of transcript records\n:record-hashes   = set used as the dedupe index\n```\n\nThat is reasonable because the transcript itself wants list semantics: ordered, append-friendly, readable as a timeline. A GitMeta set would dedupe values, but it would not naturally preserve transcript order. If we stored the whole transcript records in a set, we would need to reconstruct order from `record_index` / timestamp later, and the set would sort by value rather than by transcript sequence. That feels worse for both handoff and review browsing.\n\nThe only reason we still have app-side dedupe is that GitMeta cannot currently say “append this list entry only if this hash is not already in that set.” If we blindly appended to the list and also added to the set, the set would dedupe, but the transcript list would still grow duplicate records.\n\nSo: yes, the set is the right primitive, and we’re using it in the right role. I would describe the current design as “journal plus index,” not invented dedupe. The transcript list is the journal; `record-hashes` is the uniqueness index. That said, one future GitMeta API could make this cleaner: an atomic “append list entries guarded by set membership” operation. But I would not replace the transcript list with a set.","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-11T16:18:48.678Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}